26/08/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Government spokesman Dimitar Tsonev said on Monday (25 August) the cabinet was considering sending a civilian mission to Iraq, composed of 15 to 20 people, who would handle administrative matters related to Bulgaria's military unit there. The unit in Kerbala is under Polish command. Tsonev indicated that the issue would be discussed during Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski's current visit to Bulgaria.
In other news Monday, Foreign Minister Solomon Passy sought US assistance in getting Bulgaria's embassy in Baghdad reopened. Passy, making a one-day visit to Baghdad, led a business delegation exploring opportunities for economic co-operation with post-war Iraq. (Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa - 26/08/03; BTA, BNT, BNR, bTV - 25/08/03)
